About Me

{/* Profile Image */}
{/* About Text */}

Deepa Devangmath

I am a licensed architect from India, currently in my ninth year of studying architecture. My research delves into how space impacts human behavior and, in turn, their mental well-being. My design philosophy centers on creating harmony between context, built form, and users. I strongly believe that collaboration, empathy, and attentive listening are key to developing meaningful architectural solutions.

I have actively collaborated on various live projects and take great interest in conducting case studies of thoughtfully designed spaces, focusing on their construction methods, material choices, and zoning strategies.

{/* Additional Section */}

"Collaboration, empathy, and attentive listening are the cornerstones of great architecture."
